    realCompanyExample: 'OpenAI started as a non-profit AI research lab in 2015, launched ChatGPT in November 2022, and by 2024 was valued at $80+ billion. Microsoft has invested over $13 billion, integrating ChatGPT into Azure, Office, and Bing. The company went from research lab to one of the most valuable tech companies in the world in under 2 years.',
    visualDiagram: 'Step 1: User types prompt → Step 2: Tokenizer splits text into tokens → Step 3: Tokens enter Transformer encoder → Step 4: Self-attention computes relevance between all token pairs → Step 5: Feed-forward layers transform representations → Step 6: Output probabilities computed for next token → Step 7: Token sampled from probability distribution → Step 8: New token appended to sequence → Repeat from Step 3 until stop condition → Step 9: Full response sent to user',
    quickSummary: 'ChatGPT is a Transformer-based large language model trained on internet-scale data and fine-tuned with human feedback, generating text one token at a time by predicting the most probable next word given the conversation context.',
