    sharkTankExample: 'Swiggy founder Sriharsha Majety appeared on Shark Tank India season 2 as a guest shark, sharing insights about scaling marketplace businesses and the importance of unit economics.',
    realCompanyExample: 'Swiggy, founded in 2014, raised over $3 billion from investors like Prosus, SoftBank, and Accel. By 2024, Swiggy was valued at $10+ billion, processing 1.5+ million orders daily across 500+ cities. Zomato went public in 2021 at a $8 billion valuation and acquired Uber Eats India in 2020, consolidating the market.',
    visualDiagram: 'Step 1: User browses restaurants (location-based filtering) → Step 2: User places order → Step 3: Order sent to restaurant\'s tablet/POS → Step 4: Platform predicts prep time from historical data → Step 5: Logistics engine finds optimal delivery partner → Step 6: Delivery partner navigates to restaurant → Step 7: Food prepared → Step 8: Delivery partner picks up (matches order ID) → Step 9: Real-time GPS tracking to user\'s location → Step 10: Delivery completed → Step 11: Payment split → Step 12: Ratings & feedback collected',
    quickSummary: 'Food delivery platforms use a three-sided marketplace model with real-time logistics optimization — coordinating consumers, restaurants, and delivery partners through ML-powered assignment, route optimization, and dynamic pricing to deliver food in under 30-40 minutes.',
